# 🎯 MODULE 18: CUSTOMER MANAGEMENT

## Overview

Customer Management is the master module acting as the central repository for all onboarded clients. It converts approved leads into revenue-generating entities and provides a **360-degree view** of a customer's lifetime relationship — spanning contracts, active sites, and service history.

**Module Connections:**

- **Depends on:** Module 15 (Lead Management — for lead-to-customer conversion), Module 16 (Quotation Management — accepted quotations trigger contract creation)
- **Used by:** Module 19 (Contract Management), Module 20 (Sales Orders & Service Execution), Module 9 (Tax & Billing)
- **Triggers:** Module 19 (Contract creation on customer onboarding), Module 20 (Service orders linked to customer sites)
- **Prerequisites:** Module 15 must exist for lead-import flow; manual entry is always available as fallback

