## Deactivation Popup Fields

| Field             | Type      | Required    | Options / Validation                                                                               |
| ----------------- | --------- | ----------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Reason Dropdown   | Dropdown  | Yes         | Contract Concluded / Customer Request / Non-Payment / Bad Debt / Duplicate Entry / Other          |
| Specify Reason    | Text Area | Conditional | Required if "Other" selected; minimum 10 characters                                                |

---

## Validation Rules

| Check                    | Condition                                                   | Outcome                                              |
| ------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| Active Contract Block    | Customer has one or more contracts in "Active" status        | ❌ Block deactivation; show error message             |
| Open Sales Order Block   | Customer has one or more SOs in "Draft" or "Active" status  | ❌ Block deactivation; show error message             |
| Reason Mandatory         | Confirm Deactivation clicked without selecting a reason     | ❌ Inline error: "Please select a reason"             |
| "Other" Reason Mandatory | "Other" selected but Specify Reason is blank                | ❌ Inline error: "Please specify a reason (min 10 chars)" |

---

## Business Rules

| Rule                   | Detail                                                                                                 |
| ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| No Hard Delete         | Customer records can never be permanently deleted from the database                                    |
| Soft-Delete Only       | Deactivation sets customer status to "Inactive" and excludes them from active dropdowns and workflows  |
| Historical Preservation| All contracts, sites, SOs, and service history remain intact and accessible via the View screen (18.3) |
| Reactivation           | An Inactive customer can be reactivated by the [Reactivate] action in 18.1 (no remark required)       |
| Cascading Status       | Deactivation does NOT automatically close or alter linked sites, contracts, or orders                  |

---

## Post-Deactivation System Behaviors

| Trigger                    | System Action                                                                     |
| -------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Customer Deactivated       | Status field updated to "Inactive" across all views                               |
| Active Dropdown Removal    | Customer removed from all searchable dropdowns in new transactions (SOs, Contracts)|
| Audit Log                  | Records deactivation: Customer ID, reason, user ID, timestamp                     |
| Notification               | Notifies Branch Manager and Finance team of customer deactivation                 |
| Linked Lead (if any)       | Lead record's "Customer Status" field updated to reflect deactivation             |

